<paragraph id="F3EE5DF26BDC3CE3387D10B8D32AD4F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="82E34BD88207648958BFE7ACD6BB5FCF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Colour.</emphasis>
Head dark brown, mesosoma, petiole and postpetiole brown to brownish black, lateral sides of pronotum with indistinct brownish areas, gaster mostly brown only base of first segment slightly brighter, in the palest specimens mesosoma partly yellowish brown; scape yellowish to yellowish brown, funicle segments 1-8 yellowish, antennal club yellowish brown to dark brown, legs mostly yellowish to yellowish brown, femora medially darkened (Figs 
<figureCitation id="B905CD555EA6EAEA83AA56DB4F3F363C" captionStart="Figures 1, 2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1, 2. Holotype worker of Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 1 dorsal 2 lateral. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures1-2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666943" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="73C6B144C8ABF57CA544C75BA0881E4C" captionStart="Figures 1, 2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1, 2. Holotype worker of Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 1 dorsal 2 lateral. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures1-2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666943" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">2</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="3034FD942B071154DBCDF4454D670733" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="BF649CC6453342A74F9EE30FCD4D282D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Slightly elongate, 1.28 times as long as wide, sides below and above eyes gently convex, occipital corners regularly rounded, occipital margin of head straight (Figs 
<figureCitation id="8E51A7555BDD0A1A1C7A9D64F3F2A4A3" captionStart="Figures 3, 4" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 3, 4. Head and antennae of holotype workers 3 Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 4 Temnothorax euboeae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures3-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666944" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="CB3B3109B1FEEFF60359CB2BB55EED29" captionStart="Figures 7, 8" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 7, 8. Head sculpture of holotype workers 7 Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 8 Temnothorax euboeae sp. nov." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures7-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666946" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7</figureCitation>
). Anterior margin of clypeus distinctly convex, medial notch absent. Eyes moderate, short oval, 1.2 times as long as wide. Antennal scape short, in lateral view slightly curved, 0.78 times as long as length of the head, in apex gradually widened, its base without tooth, funiculus long, club 3-segmented (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3EA4B98E18D54E9FAC11B6A43AF09269" captionStart="Figures 3, 4" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 3, 4. Head and antennae of holotype workers 3 Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 4 Temnothorax euboeae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures3-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666944" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3</figureCitation>
). Surface of scape finely microreticulate, shiny, covered with thin, dense, decumbent to suberect setae. Funicle longer than scape, first segment 2.1 times as long as wide at apex, segments 2-7 short, rectangular. Mandibles rounded with thick and sparse striae, shiny. Clypeus with sharp median longitudinal keel and two keels laterally, area between keels microreticulate but shiny. Frontal carinae short, slightly extending beyond frontal lobes. Antennal fossa deep, with thin circular striae and dense microreticulation. Frontal lobes narrow, microreticulate with costulae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="825E3EC5F39D26E01661D7CB7050242D" captionStart="Figures 7, 8" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 7, 8. Head sculpture of holotype workers 7 Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 8 Temnothorax euboeae sp. nov." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures7-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666946" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7</figureCitation>
). Frons, gena, malar region, vertex and temples densely reticulate with shiny interspaces; frons, gena, area behind eyes, central part of vertex, occipital area with additional costulae, malar area with costulae partly interrupted. Whole surface of head appears shiny. Sides of head with very short and sparse adpressed pubescence, sides of frons, vertex and occipital area with erect, pale, short and thick setae (Figs 
<figureCitation id="5D6B76AA21E0C1EB7A3ABF60696403FE" captionStart="Figures 3, 4" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 3, 4. Head and antennae of holotype workers 3 Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 4 Temnothorax euboeae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures3-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666944" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="6F8FE5D6E1C5C6283F4A1D4F44B4C818" captionStart="Figures 7, 8" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 7, 8. Head sculpture of holotype workers 7 Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 8 Temnothorax euboeae sp. nov." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures7-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666946" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="03D25ED9E1D32D2CE42EA94E77D2E8A5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="D55EF61067DC3A6CA5D1E7E9C5BAF687" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Elongate, approximately twice as long as wide, distinctly arched in profile. Metanotal groove absent. Pronotum convex on sides. Propodeal spines very short, in form of triangular denticles or small angulation (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CE739CA1A92F2B9577C321627935881B" captionStart="Figures 1, 2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1, 2. Holotype worker of Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 1 dorsal 2 lateral. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures1-2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666943" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">2</figureCitation>
). Whole surface of mesosoma densely reticulate with shiny interspaces. Pronotal dorsum regulate, lateral sides of pronotum rugocostulate, mesonotal dorsum reticulocostulate, propodeum rugocostulate, area below spines microreticulate with few transverse costulae. Entire mesosoma with erect, pale, moderately long and thick setae (Figs 
<figureCitation id="4D5064C52E34DC8B66B2630EDFB95DB9" captionStart="Figures 1, 2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1, 2. Holotype worker of Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 1 dorsal 2 lateral. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures1-2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666943" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="4760E897620A028ACE380F1D6B57FCE7" captionStart="Figures 1, 2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1, 2. Holotype worker of Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 1 dorsal 2 lateral. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures1-2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666943" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">2</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B7026BF83CE1F2DCE3B051EB549C2680" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="1CAB19544E132324F7C7CF590F901939" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Petiole</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
In lateral view, with moderately elongate peduncle, node low, with anterior face shallowly concave and dorsum regularly rounded, whole surface rugoreticulate. Dorsal surface with sparse, short, erect setae. 
<emphasis id="8058284E4939B23A78F0FDC0692B8751" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="4C73D49D9FCA52083100EF7EACE5835B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Postpetiole</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
In lateral view regularly convex, sides rounded, on the whole surface reticulocostulate, surface appears less rugose than surface of petiole. Dorsal surface with sparse, moderately long, erect setae (Figs 
<figureCitation id="8FADCAAC9EF7DBEB708EBF37C4466D5E" captionStart="Figures 1, 2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1, 2. Holotype worker of Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 1 dorsal 2 lateral. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures1-2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666943" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="AF7416BAFFD3B290DAE06E38DC9016C0" captionStart="Figures 1, 2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1, 2. Holotype worker of Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 1 dorsal 2 lateral. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures1-2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666943" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">2</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="5901B28DD600D54B4D7BC7B0C0F6E8C7" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="8B2085034F6A324EEEAEC697C1E6D696" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Gaster</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Smooth and shiny, with erect, thin, pale setae (Figs 
<figureCitation id="E7380606C5CC565FC69B0F7DB46A48E5" captionStart="Figures 1, 2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1, 2. Holotype worker of Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 1 dorsal 2 lateral. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures1-2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666943" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1436C0AA390311DA66A24AA54EA4FEFD" captionStart="Figures 1, 2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1, 2. Holotype worker of Temnothorax arkasi sp. nov. 1 dorsal 2 lateral. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79085.figures1-2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666943" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">2</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="E2529C8A67750C290B2F8E10E8D7159D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="0AE12EA8600787FB544A927374A201CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Legs</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Moderately elongate, femora swollen in the middle, tibiae widened from base to 
<normalizedToken id="5F7A4635130AA2380C943CC7E2FB3A3B" originalValue="¾">3/4</normalizedToken>
length, surface of legs covered with sparse, adpressed to decumbent hairs.
</paragraph>
